Table 1. EigenWorms dataset: mean ? standard deviation of test 
set accuracy measured over three repeats. Also reported are the 
mean memory usage and training time. For all models a variety 
of step sizes are considered. For the Neural RDE we additionally 
investigate varying depths. (Recalling that the NCDE is a depth-1 
NRDE.) '-' denotes that the model could not be run within GPU 
memory. Bold denotes the best model score for a given step size, 
and  *  denotes that the score was the best achieved over all models 
and step sizes.
